#import "preamble.typ": *
#show: preamble
#align(center, [== Notation])
This document uses the following notational conventions:
-
  $A equiv^alpha B$ denotes that $A$ and $B$ are $alpha$-equivalent.
-
  $A equiv^(arrow_eta) B$ denotes that $A$ $eta$-reduces to $B$, while $B equiv^(gets_eta) A$ denotes that $B$ $eta$-expands to $A$.
-
  The projection maps from a product/pair type are denoted $pi_k$.
